data.meta_description:
103 likes, 8 comments - summerstage on August 29, 2020: "The Charlie Parker Jazz Festival was born in 2003 from a community grassroots initiative to celebrate @charliebirdparkerofficial and the cultural influence of jazz in New York City. In the course of 17 years the #CharlieParkerJazzFest has become an institution in New York City and across the globe as we unite jazz contemporaries and legends.
--
Tune in at 4 PM ET on your fav social channel (Instagram, Facebook, Youtube or Twitch) for the world premiere of our short film ‚ÄúCharlie Parker At 100: A Celebration of Parker‚Äôs Birthday and the Charlie Parker Jazz Festival‚Äù - showcasing conversations with festival founder Sam Turvey, saxophonist @jaleelshaw, pianist @thejasonmoran, and more from the neighborhood Parker lived.
